                        1904
                    ],
                    "type": "text",
                    "lines": [
                        {
                            "bbox": [
                                198,
                                1659,
                                1252,
                                1904
                            ],
                            "spans": [
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        198,
                                        1659,
                                        1252,
                                        1904
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "MARLIN is implemented on top of the RL Baselines3 Zoo (RL- Zoo3) [20] framework, which follows best practices for using Stable- Baselines3 (SB3) [21], a PyTorch [22]- based library that implements state- of- the- art RL algorithms following the OpenAI gym interface [23]."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ],
                    "index": 4
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        204,
                        1904,
                        1252,
                        2448
                    ],
                    "type": "text",
                    "lines": [
                        {
                            "bbox": [
                                204,
                                1904,
                                1252,
                                2448
                            ],
                            "spans": [
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        204,
                                        1904,
                                        1252,
                                        2448
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "1) State: Table "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        204,
                                        1904,
                                        1252,
                                        2448
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "\\mathbb{I}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        204,
                                        1904,
                                        1252,
                                        2448
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " describes the state encoded in MARLIN. 14 features are gathered during the time frame that follows the action taken at step "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        204,
                                        1904,
                                        1252,
                                        2448
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "t - 1"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        204,
                                        1904,
                                        1252,
                                        2448
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " .MARLIN then augments the state space with 7 statistics, i.e., last, mean, standard deviation, minimum, maximum, Exponential Moving Average (EMA), and difference from the previous state "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        204,
                                        1904,
                                        1252,
                                        2448
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "s_{t - 1}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        204,
                                        1904,
                                        1252,
                                        2448
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " , that are computed for each of the 14 features. The previous "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        204,
                                        1904,
                                        1252,
                                        2448
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "N"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        204,
                                        1904,
                                        1252,
                                        2448
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " states are also stacked together to form a history of the previous observations, attempting to adhere to the Markov property. The final state served to the agent will then have "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        204,
                                        1904,
                                        1252,
                                        2448
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "N\\times |F e a t u r e s|\\times |S t a t s|"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        204,
                                        1904,
                                        1252,
                                        2448
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " features. This totals up to 980 different features."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ],
