                                        2204,
                                        2346,
                                        2399
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "A strictly negative reward function promotes the agent to accumulate the smallest amount of penalties. The penalty received is much smaller the closer the agent it is, at each step, to having utilized the link to the best of its possibilities."
                                }
                            ]
