                                        2402,
                                        2351,
                                        2798
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "The careful reader might notice that such rewarding system encourages the agent to accumulate acked bytes regardless explicit impact on the RTT, falling into the risk of privileging actions that could produce more acked bytes in the immediate future, with the drawback of causing undesired queuing delays. To prevent such risk, we consider a second formulation of the reward function that introduces a RTT- based penalty coefficient:"
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ],
